accessrestrict.head: Access
accessrestrict.p: COLLECTION STORED OFF-SITE AT SRLF: Open for research. Advance notice required for access. Contact the UCLA Library Special Collections Reference Desk for paging information.

userestrict.head: Publication Rights
userestrict.p: Copyright of portions of this collection has been assigned to The Regents of the University of California. The UCLA University Archives can grant permission to publish for materials to which it holds the copyright. All requests for permission to publish or quote must be submitted in writing to the UCLA University Archivist.

phystech.head: Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements
phystech.p: COLLECTION CONTAINS DIGITAL MATERIALS: Special equipment or further processing may be required for viewing. TO access digital materials you must notify the reference desk in advance of your visit. COLLECTION CONTAINS AUDIOVISUAL MATERIALS: Audiovisual materials in this collection will require assessment and possible digitization for safe access. All requests to access special collections materials must be made in advance using the request button located on this page.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Collections are processed to a variety of levels depending on the work necessary to make them usable, their perceived user interest and research value, availability of staff and resources, and competing priorities. Library Special Collections provides a standard level of preservation and access for all collections and, when time and resources permit, conducts more intensive processing. These materials have been arranged and described according to national and local standards and best practices.

We are committed to providing ethical, inclusive, and anti-racist description of the materials we steward, and to remediating existing description of our materials that contains language that may be offensive or cause harm. We invite you to submit feedback about how our collections are described, and how they could be described more accurately, by filling out the form located on our website: Report Potentially Offensive Description in Library Special Collections.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Record Series 377 contains the administrative files of the UCLA University Librarian, generated between 1919 and 1998, including those of John E. Goodwin, Lawrence Clark Powell, and Robert Vosper. Files regard such topics as library departments; branch libraries; interaction and cooperation with UCLA academic departments, other University of California campuses, libraries, universities, and institutions; acquisitions; budgets; committees; associations and societies; Library Council; Northern and Southern Regional Library Boards; Special Collections; programs and conferences; contracts; grants; the use and need of space; library visitors; bibliographers; OCLC (Online Computer Library Center, Inc., formerly the Ohio College Library Center); lending privileges; public library catalogs; and blanket purchase orders. Also included are the chronological files of James R. Cox (Acting Associate University Librarian for Public Services, 1977-1979; Assistant to the University Librarian, 1979-1983). Materials include correspondence, statistics, reports (annual, semiannual, quarterly, and monthly from library departments and branch libraries), meeting agendas and minutes, forms, manuals, and other operational materials.
This is an active record series; additional University records are expected to be added.
